name: Yogurt

comment_expert: Using the powder milk DIAAS as a approximation. Milk and yogurt contain both 80% casein, 20% whey, however the lactic fermentation could transform the proteins - for the better or the worse. (yogurt is cooked then fermented milk)

name: Cottage cheese
greenhouse_gas_ref: Fresh cream cheese, plain, around 3% fat
comment_expert: Using the powder milk DIAAS as a approximation. Milk and cottage cheese contain both 80% casein, 20% whey, however the lactic fermentation could transform the proteins - for the better or the worse. (cottage cheese is cooked then fermented milk)
greenhouse_gas_comment_expert: At this stage I don't undertsand how the cottage cheese carbon footprint per g of protein can be better than the figure for milk while all the proteins come from the milk and there is an additional cost for the transformation. To be verified
